					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I have literature on both RF transmitters and television receivers from the mid-1950s, when color NTSC was introduced. I don't think that's pertinent though, because it's too old.<br /><br />As for filters, most materials on that subject, on-line or in print, expect way too many things to be known by the reader, are gratuitously formalistic, at the same time offensively imprecise in terminology and prose, and generally are not suited for people who just want to skim trying to find what they need. Of course, I say that about pretty much any mathematical subject, so who am I to complain.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

