				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Unfortunately, the vast majority of the service manuals and schematics I can find are either from the very early days of TV, where everything was <a href="https://www.antiqueradio.org/PhilcoH3412LPredictaTelevision.htm" class="postlink">valve-based and monochrome</a>, or from after the VLSI revolution and all the TVs do all the interesting signal processing stuff inside a monolithic encapsulated silicon die.<br /><br />Doing my best to read the valve-based schematic for the Predicta 10L4x chassis, I think it just completely ignores the modulated audio signal altogether and relies on the temporal and spatial bandwidth to hide any crosstalk.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

